cts.","pos":[8327,8448]},{"content":"To enumerate visual objects in a visual tree use the <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Media.VisualTreeHelper.HitTest%2A&gt;</ph> method with a hit test callback function.","pos":[8449,8599],"source":" To enumerate visual objects in a visual tree use the <xref:System.Windows.Media.VisualTreeHelper.HitTest%2A> method with a hit test callback function."},{"content":"The hit test callback function is called by the system when the coordinate value you specify is contained in a visual object.","pos":[8600,8725]},{"content":"During the hit test results enumeration, you should not perform any operation that modifies the visual tree.","pos":[8732,8840]},{"content":"Adding or removing an object from the visual tree while it is being traversed can result in unpredictable behavior.","pos":[8841,8956]},{"content":"You can safely modify the visual tree after the <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Media.VisualTreeHelper.HitTest%2A&gt;</ph> method returns.","pos":[8957,9076],"source":" You can safely modify the visual tree after the <xref:System.Windows.Media.VisualTreeHelper.HitTest%2A> method returns."},{"content":"You may want to provide a data structure, such as an <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Collections.ArrayList&gt;</ph>, to store values during the hit test results enumeration.","pos":[9077,9223],"source":" You may want to provide a data structure, such as an <xref:System.Collections.ArrayList>, to store values during the hit test results enumeration."},{"content":"The hit test callback method defines the actions you perform when a hit test is identified on a particular visual object in the visual tree.","pos":[9499,9639]},{"content":"After you perform the actions, you return a <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Media.HitTestResultBehavior&gt;</ph> value that determines whether to continue the enumeration of any other visual objects or not.","pos":[9640,9827],"source":" After you perform the actions, you return a <xref:Sys